c("Enhance the enabling environment and increase access to finance for MSMEs. Lack of financing and weaknesses in the financial environment constrain MSME growth. MSMEs are the backbone of the Guatemalan economy, contributing to 40 percent of GDP and 77 percent of the workforce. However, access to finance remains an important challenge, undermining the competitiveness and productivity of MSMEs. The lack of financing instruments, particularly loans, suitable for MSMEs hinder firm investment and growth, mainly because MSME financing is perceived by financial institutions as a high risk lending activity, to a large extent due to the degree of informality and vulnerability to domestic and external shocks associated with MSMEs. The WBG seeks to catalyze productive opportunities for greater employment, through increased access to finance for the country\x92s MSMEs. The expected outcome of this objective is to enhance the enabling environment and increase access to finance, so as to expand income and employment opportunities in the long-term. 3.1 Number of <span id = "word">Microfinance</span> and SME finance loans provided through financial services:  Baseline: 93,133 (2015) Target:  141,723 (2020)", 
